    "body": "### Problem\n\nHello !\n\nIn Neovim with a vertical split (e.g. in `diff` mode or using `nvim -O file1 file2`) the last character of the status line (that is the character just under the windows separator) seems to be treated differently from the rest of the status line, and doesn't change its highlight according to `FocusLost`: the highlight stays `StatusLine` and never becomes `StatusLineNC`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Configuration in `init.vim`:\n\n```\nautocmd FocusGained,WinEnter,VimEnter * setlocal statusline=%#StatusLine#%F\\ [%{strlen(&fenc)?&fenc:'Aucun\\ encodage'}]\\ %m%=%l/%L,%c\\ [%p%%]\nautocmd FocusLost,WinLeave,Bufread * setlocal statusline=%#StatusLineNC#%F\\ [%{strlen(&fenc)?&fenc:'Aucun\\ encodage'}]\\ %m%=%l/%L,%c\\ [%p%%]\n```\n\n2. `nvim -O file1 file2`\n3. The statusline of the left window (with the `file1` buffer) has the `StatusLine` highlight; the other window (`file2`) has the `StatusLineNC` highlight. That is the expected behavior.\n4. Open another software: both windows have the `StatusLineNC` highlight, but the last character of the left window (`file1`) under the window separator (so just under `VertSplit`) is still highlighted with `StatusLine`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe entire statusline, including the last character under the `VertSplit`, should be highlighted like the rest of the status line.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.4\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.1.1120 (`FocusLost` doesn't seem to work at all)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArchLinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst 0.9.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nsystem package manager (`pacman -S neovim`)",
